Implemented single login and location APIs.

Modified: POST /api/v1/serviceProviders/signup
- username now required to be unique across customer and service provider tables  #DONE

Modified: POST /api/v1/customers/signup
- username now required to be unique across customer and service provider tables

Modified: POST | PUT /api/v1/customers/<cus_id>/profile/edit
- username now required to be unique across customer and service provider tables  #DONE

Modified: POST | PUT /api/v1/serviceProviders/<sp_id>/profile/edit
- username now required to be unique across customer and service provider tables  #DONE

New API: POST /api/v1/login
- implement a single login endpoint for both customers and service providers

Deprecated:
- POST api/v1/customers/login
- POST /api/v1/serviceProviders/login
- use POST /api/v1/login instead

New API: GET /api/v1/countries
- returns a list of all countries in the form:
 ```{"name": <country name>, "id": <country ID>}```

New API: GET /api/v1/countries/<country_id>/states
- returns a list of all states in the specified country in the form:
 ```{"name": <state name>, "id": <state ID>}, "country_name": <country name>, "country_id": <country ID>}```

New API: GET /api/v1/countries/<country_id>/states/<state_id>/locations
- returns a list of all locations in the specified state in the form:
 ```{"name": <location name>, "id": <location ID>}, "state_name": <state name>, "state_id": <state ID>, "country_name": <country name>, "country_id": <country ID>}```
